{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"PaymentMethodChangeEvent","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentMethodChangeEvent","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Payment_Request_API\">Payment Request API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentMethodChangeEvent\"><code>PaymentMethodChangeEvent</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentMethodChangeEvent/methodDetails\"><code>methodDetails</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentMethodChangeEvent/methodName\"><code>methodName</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentRequestUpdateEvent\"><code>PaymentRequestUpdateEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\"><code>Event</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Payment Request API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLIFrameElement/allowPaymentRequest\"><code>HTMLIFrameElement.allowPaymentRequest</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MerchantValidationEvent\"><code>MerchantValidationEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentAddress\"><code>PaymentAddress</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentRequest\"><code>PaymentRequest</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentRequestUpdateEvent\"><code>PaymentRequestUpdateEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentResponse\"><code>PaymentResponse</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard secure\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\">secure contexts</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div>\n<p>The <strong><code>PaymentMethodChangeEvent</code></strong> interface of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Payment_Request_API\">Payment Request API</a> describes the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentRequest/paymentmethodchange_event\" title=\"paymentmethodchange\"><code>paymentmethodchange</code></a> event which is fired by some payment handlers when the user switches payment instruments (e.g., a user selects a \"store\" card to make a purchase while using Apple Pay).</p><svg viewBox=\"-1 -1 650 42\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin meet\">\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\">\n    <rect x=\"0\" y=\"0\" width=\"75\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"37.5\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      Event\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"75\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"105\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" \"=\"\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"75,14 85,9 85,19 75,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentRequestUpdateEvent\">\n    <rect x=\"105\" y=\"0\" width=\"200\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"205\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      PaymentRequestUpdateEvent\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"305\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"335\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" \"=\"\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"305,14 315,9 315,19 305,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentMethodChangeEvent\" aria-current=\"page\">\n    <rect x=\"335\" y=\"0\" width=\"192\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#F4F7F8\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"431\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      PaymentMethodChangeEvent\n    </text>\n  </a></svg>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"constructor","title":"Constructor","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"paymentmethodchangeevent\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentMethodChangeEvent/PaymentMethodChangeEvent\" title=\"PaymentMethodChangeEvent()\"><code>PaymentMethodChangeEvent()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Creates and returns a new <code>PaymentMethodChangeEvent</code> object, optionally initialized with values taken from a given <a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>PaymentMethodChangeEventInit</code></a> dictionary.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"properties","title":"Properties","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>In addition to the properties below, this interface includes properties inherited from <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentRequestUpdateEvent\"><code>PaymentRequestUpdateEvent</code></a>.</em></p>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"methoddetails\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentMethodChangeEvent/methodDetails\" title=\"methodDetails\"><code>methodDetails</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span> <span class=\"notecard inline secure\" title=\"This feature is available only in secure contexts (HTTPS)\">Secure context</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An object containing payment method-specific data useful when handling a payment method change. If no such information is available, this value is <code>null</code>.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"methodname\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentMethodChangeEvent/methodName\" title=\"methodName\"><code>methodName</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span> <span class=\"notecard inline secure\" title=\"This feature is available only in secure contexts (HTTPS)\">Secure context</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A string containing the payment method identifier, a string which uniquely identifies a particular payment method. This identifier is usually a URL used during the payment process, but may be a standardized non-URL string as well, such as <code>basic-card</code>. The default value is the empty string, <code>\"\"</code>.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methods","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>This interface includes methods inherited from <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentRequestUpdateEvent\"><code>PaymentRequestUpdateEvent</code></a>.</em></p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/payment-request/#paymentmethodchangeevent-interface","title":"Payment Request API"}],"query":"api.PaymentMethodChangeEvent"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.PaymentMethodChangeEvent","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PaymentMethodChangeEvent/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Constructor","id":"constructor"},{"text":"Properties","id":"properties"},{"text":"Methods","id":"methods"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The PaymentMethodChangeEvent interface of the Payment Request API describes the paymentmethodchange event which is fired by some payment handlers when the user switches payment instruments (e.g., a user selects a \"store\" card to make a purchase while using Apple Pay).","popularity":0.0002,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:17:24.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"PaymentMethodChangeEvent","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/paymentmethodchangeevent","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/paymentmethodchangeevent/index.md","last_commit_url":